%% MLflow Operator - Data Flow Diagram
%% Generated by: Claude Opus 4.6

sequenceDiagram
    participant Admin as Platform Admin
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Operator as MLflow Operator<br/>controller-runtime
    participant Helm as Helm Renderer<br/>(in-process)
    participant Client as External Client
    participant Gateway as data-science-gateway<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS
    participant MLflow as MLflow Server<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS TLS
    participant DB as PostgreSQL/MySQL<br/>5432/3306 TCP
    participant S3 as S3/GCS/Azure<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Prom as Prometheus

    Note over Admin,Helm: Flow 1: MLflow CR Reconciliation
    Admin->>K8sAPI: Create MLflow CR (cluster-scoped)
    K8sAPI->>Operator: Watch notification (HTTPS/TLS)
    Operator->>Helm: Render chart with CR spec values
    Helm-->>Operator: Kubernetes manifests
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Server-Side Apply (SSA)<br/>Deployment, Service, SA, PVC,<br/>NetworkPolicy, ClusterRole
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create HTTPRoute (if CRD exists)<br/>Create ConsoleLink (if CRD exists)

    Note over Client,S3: Flow 2: External Client to MLflow (via Gateway API)
    Client->>Gateway: HTTPS/443<br/>TLS 1.2+
    Gateway->>MLflow: HTTPS/8443<br/>TLS passthrough (service-ca cert)
    MLflow->>K8sAPI: SubjectAccessReview<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS<br/>Client SA token (forwarded)
    K8sAPI-->>MLflow: SAR result (allow/deny)
    MLflow-->>Gateway: API Response
    Gateway-->>Client: JSON Response

    Note over MLflow,S3: Flow 3: MLflow to Backend Storage
    MLflow->>DB: Metadata queries<br/>TCP (TLS optional)<br/>URI credentials
    DB-->>MLflow: Query results
    MLflow->>S3: Artifact storage<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS<br/>Cloud credentials
    S3-->>MLflow: Artifact data

    Note over Prom,Operator: Flow 4: Prometheus Metrics Scraping
    Prom->>Operator: GET /metrics<br/>HTTPS/8443 TLS<br/>Bearer Token (SA token)
    Operator-->>Prom: Metrics data
